/// section
h2: Quick start

col:
  h3: 1. Create a client
  p: Initialize with your broker URL and an optional namespace prefix. Credentials are read from environment variables by default.

col:
  h3: 2. Define your events
  p: Use the TypeScript generic or Go struct tag to attach a schema. Fluxline validates before publishing and narrows the type on receive.

col:
  h3: 3. Publish and subscribe
  p: publish() is fire-and-forget with an optional ack callback. subscribe() returns an async iterator or a channel, depending on the language.

/// section
h2: Configuration reference

col:
  h3: brokerUrl
  p: Required. WebSocket or TCP URL for your message broker.

col:
  h3: namespace
  p: Optional string prefix applied to all stream names. Useful for multi-tenant deployments.

col:
  h3: maxRetries
  p: Default 3. How many times to retry a failed publish before raising an error.

col:
  h3: ackTimeout
  p: Default 5000 ms. Time to wait for a broker ack before treating the publish as failed.


